SKUKUZA – An alleged poacher was arrested soon after being trampled by elephants in the Kruger National Park earlier today. According to SANParks media specialist, the man was confirmed to be part of a poaching group. “He was arrested by the SAPS after he was injured while running away from elephants,” Phaahla said. The incident happened on the S21. Also read: UPDATE: Eight alleged land invaders arrested at Plaston 